The paper discusses research directions in the area of Principles of Data Management (PDM), which is a subfield of computer science that deals with the principles and techniques for managing large amounts of data. This makes cs.DB the most likely category. The paper also mentions the potential practical relevance of the research directions, which suggests a focus on security and privacy (cs.CR), algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), information retrieval (cs.IR), and software engineering (cs.SE).
